"Beccali M., Cellura M., Iudicello M., Mistretta M.","Resource consumption and environmental impacts of the agrofood sector: Life cycle assessment of italian citrus-based products",2009,"Environmental Management","43","4",,"707","724",,,10.1007/s00267-008-9251-y,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-62549153515&partnerID=40&md5=dad83809a11e9d05893d15de6afda6d6","Dipartimento di Ricerche Energetiche e Ambientali (DREAM), Università di Palermo, Viale delle Scienze, 90128 Palermo, Italy; Dipartimento di Arte, Scienza e Tecnica Del Costruire (DASTEC), Università Mediterranea di Reggio Calabria, Salita Melissari, Reggio Calabria 89124, Italy","Beccali, M., Dipartimento di Ricerche Energetiche e Ambientali (DREAM), Università di Palermo, Viale delle Scienze, 90128 Palermo, Italy; Cellura, M., Dipartimento di Ricerche Energetiche e Ambientali (DREAM), Università di Palermo, Viale delle Scienze, 90128 Palermo, Italy; Iudicello, M., Dipartimento di Ricerche Energetiche e Ambientali (DREAM), Università di Palermo, Viale delle Scienze, 90128 Palermo, Italy; Mistretta, M., Dipartimento di Arte, Scienza e Tecnica Del Costruire (DASTEC), Università Mediterranea di Reggio Calabria, Salita Melissari, Reggio Calabria 89124, Italy","Food production and consumption cause significant environmental burdens during the product life cycles. As a result of intensive development and the changing social attitudes and behaviors in the last century, the agrofood sector is the highest resource consumer after housing in the EU. This paper is part of an effort to estimate environmental impacts associated with life cycles of the agrofood chain, such as primary energy consumption, water exploitation, and global warming. Life cycle assessment is used to investigate the production of the following citrus-based products in Italy: essential oil, natural juice, and concentrated juice from oranges and lemons. The related process flowcharts, the relevant mass and energy flows, and the key environmental issues are identified for each product. This paper represents one of the first studies on the environmental impacts from cradle to gate for citrus products in order to suggest feasible strategies and actions to improve their environmental performance. © 2009 Springer Science+Business Media, LLC.","Agrofood; Citrus; Energy; Juice; Life cycle assessment; Resource depletion; Water","Agrofood; Citrus; Energy; Juice; Life cycle assessment; Resource depletion; Environmental impact; Global warming; Water resources; Life cycle; energy use; environmental effect; European Union; evergreen tree; food industry; global warming; life cycle analysis; resource use; water use; Agriculture; Citrus; Conservation of Natural Resources; Environment; Food Industry; Italy; Citrus",,,,,,"(2001) Rules for Environmental Product Declaration, , ANPA (Italian Agency for Environment Protection) July ANPA, Rome (in Italian); Ardente, F., Beccali, G., Cellura, M., Marvuglia, A., POEMS: A case study of an italian wine-producing firm (2006) Environmental Management, 38, pp. 350-364. , 3; Ardente, F., Beccali, M., Cellura, M., Mistretta, M., Building energy performance: A LCA case study of kenaf-fibres insulation board (2008) Energy and Buildings, 40, pp. 1-10. , 1; (2001) Regional Decree. Piano di Sviluppo Rurale-Normale Buona Pratica Agricola, , Assessorato Agricoltura e Foreste January Assessorato Agricoltura e Foreste, Catanzaro, January 24 (in Italian); (2001), Boustead Consulting Ltd. Boustead Consulting Ltd. West Sussex, UKBringezu, S., Behrensmeier, R., (1998), Kluwer Academic Dordrecht, NetherlandsBrower, M., Leon, W., Practical advice from the Union of Concerned Scientists (1999) The Consumers Guide to Effective Environmental Choices, , Three Rivers Press, New York; Carlsson-Kanayma, A., Climate change and dietary choices: How can emissions of greenhouse gases from food consumption be reduced (1998) Food Policy, 23, pp. 277-293. , 3-4; Carlsson-Kanyama, A., Ekstrom, M.P., Shanahan